Johannesburg Gautrain services are back on track after a brief interruption that happened on Thursday morning due to a train failure. The interruption happened at around 8:30am on Thursday and forced commuters to use the bus service provided by Gautrain to get from Hatfield to Pretoria stations.Gautrain spokesperson Kesagee Nayager said in a statement that train services between Hatfield and Pretoria stations were, on Friday, functioning at normal 15 minute intervals at peak period. &quot;The train service to all other Gautrain stations remain fully operational and according to schedule. We thank passengers for their patience and understanding and sincerely apologise for the inconvenience&quot;, Nayager said. The Star